{
  "title": "Benchmarking Event-Driven Systems Using FastAPI with Python 3.12+",
  "summary": "This guide demonstrates how to benchmark the performance of an event-driven system built with FastAPI and Python 3.12+ using popular tools like Uvicorn and aiohttp.",

  "key_points": [
    "Understand the importance of benchmarking in evaluating the efficiency of your event-driven system",
    "Set up the development environment for a FastAPI application with Python 3.12+",
    "Explore two popular asyncio web servers: Uvicorn and aiohttp",
    "Learn how to use profiling tools like cProfile, line_profiler, and black-profiling",
    "Understand the differences in performance between Uvicorn and aiohttp",
    "Implement techniques for improving your FastAPI application's performance"
  ],

  "code_examples": [
    {
      "language": "Python",
      "code": "```python\nfrom fastapi import FastAPI\napp = FastAPI()\n@app.get('/')\ndef main():\tpass\nif __name__ == "__main__":\tapp.run(\"uvicorn.run\", host=\"127.0.0.1\", port=8000, log_level=\"info\")\n```"
    },
    {
      "language": "Python",
      "code": "```python\nimport uvicorn\nuvicorn.run(\"main:app\", host=\"127.0.0.1\", port=8000, log_level=\"info\")\n```"
    },
    {
      "language": "Python",
      "code": "```python\naiohttp.web.run_app(\"main:app\".wsgi_app(), host='127.0.0.1', port=8000)\n```"
    }
  ],

  "version_notes": [
    "Python 3.12+ is required for this tutorial as it includes improvements in the asyncio library.",
    "FastAPI 0.69.0 or later is recommended to use with Python 3.12.",
    "Uvicorn 0.17.0 or later and aiohttp 3.8.0 or later are required for serving the FastAPI application."
  ],

  "caveats": [
    "Results may vary depending on the complexity of your FastAPI application, hardware specifications, and other factors.",
